init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig's house was so strong that the wolf couldn't blow it down.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He went to the 92nd little pig's house and said, "Little pig, little pig, let me come in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The 92nd little pig was like, "No way, wolf.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "No, I won't.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf drank the cup of tea and said, "Little pig, little pig, let me come in.

actions.text: The 92nd little pig said, "There aren't any biskies.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Oh, I'm sorry," said the 92nd little pig.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf went out the door and into the night.
